city more dramatically.

01:16:27.760 --> 01:16:28.260
Next.

01:16:31.640 --> 01:16:33.080
This is an MIT--

01:16:33.080 --> 01:16:35.210
we're talking about
education now--

01:16:35.210 --> 01:16:39.230
this isn't an MIT project
called Signs and Lights which

01:16:39.230 --> 01:16:42.380
says one of the
things we can do is

01:16:42.380 --> 01:16:47.450
create much more intelligence
in the built formal environment.

01:16:50.430 --> 01:16:54.770
The project on the right argues
for the coloring of the road

01:16:54.770 --> 01:16:58.460
surface to provide,
to indicate that you

01:16:58.460 --> 01:17:01.110
can travel at different speeds.

01:17:01.110 --> 01:17:01.610
Next.

01:17:05.340 --> 01:17:11.690
A project in Genoa, in Italy,
in which a neighborhood is

01:17:11.690 --> 01:17:16.520
cleared, and only the fossils,
the essential elements

01:17:16.520 --> 01:17:18.890
of the neighborhood
are maintained,

01:17:18.890 --> 01:17:21.500
giving the people an
understanding of what

01:17:21.500 --> 01:17:23.270
they've got to work with.

01:17:23.270 --> 01:17:26.000
On the basis of
their understanding,

01:17:26.000 --> 01:17:30.440
they precipitate
reactions, create changes,

01:17:30.440 --> 01:17:32.600
produce changes, which
are on the right.

01:17:35.160 --> 01:17:35.660
Next.

01:17:39.910 --> 01:17:45.820
Cedric Price's work in England,
the idea of building places

01:17:45.820 --> 01:17:47.990
where people can--

01:17:47.990 --> 01:17:50.800
this is prior to social media.

01:17:50.800 --> 01:17:54.250
This is actually making
places in the city--

01:17:54.250 --> 01:17:57.430
the one on the right is
called the Fun Palace,

01:17:57.430 --> 01:18:02.410
and the one on the left is
called the Interaction Center--

01:18:02.410 --> 01:18:05.500
where people randomly
could meet each other

01:18:05.500 --> 01:18:11.080
and partake of joyous activity.

01:18:11.080 --> 01:18:13.360
Next.

01:18:13.360 --> 01:18:19.990
This is a Bedford Stuyvesant New
York project, a Ford Foundation

01:18:19.990 --> 01:18:25.510
study, which is interesting.

01:18:25.510 --> 01:18:28.570
The project is to insert
a new community college

01:18:28.570 --> 01:18:35.860
in a very poor area, and
instead of building a new campus

01:18:35.860 --> 01:18:42.790
with glass buildings,
the form of the building,

01:18:42.790 --> 01:18:47.080
the inserted buildings, are
within the existing framework

01:18:47.080 --> 01:18:47.620
of the town.

01:18:54.572 --> 01:18:57.970
All the facilities that are
built for the community college

01:18:57.970 --> 01:19:00.860
are shared by the community.

01:19:00.860 --> 01:19:05.170
In fact, the curriculum
for the community college

01:19:05.170 --> 01:19:09.550
is set by the needs
of the community.

01:19:09.550 --> 01:19:12.340
The sports facilities up
on the top on the left

01:19:12.340 --> 01:19:15.910
are all partly
for the community,

01:19:15.910 --> 01:19:17.630
partly for the students.

01:19:17.630 --> 01:19:18.130
Next.

01:19:21.490 --> 01:19:25.930
The park in Philadelphia
on the left.

01:19:25.930 --> 01:19:31.180
The city, the school
without walls.

01:19:31.180 --> 01:19:36.220
The city has got enough
input, education input in it

01:19:36.220 --> 01:19:40.400
to serve as a school.

01:19:40.400 --> 01:19:40.900
Next.

01:19:43.550 --> 01:19:48.060
Metro Education
Project in Montreal,

